# Vanilla JavaScript Only

This rule enforces the use of vanilla Code without any external libraries or dependencies.

## Rules

- No external JavaScript libraries or frameworks
- No npm packages or dependencies
- No CDN imports
- No external CSS frameworks
- Use only built-in JavaScript APIs and browser APIs
- Use only native HTML5 and CSS3 features

## Allowed
- Native JavaScript (ES6+)
- Built-in browser APIs (DOM, Fetch, WebStorage, etc.)
- Native HTML5 elements and attributes
- Native CSS3 features
- Self-contained JavaScript code

## Not Allowed
- External JavaScript libraries
- npm packages
- CDN imports
- External CSS frameworks
- Third-party dependencies